Basic datatypes
string, int , bool, float etc..
int,  int8 = only take value between 0 to 128 =  uint8 = same but take only +ve values, cap = 225

aggregate datatypes  
Arrays and structs are called aggregate because they aggregate (collect) multiple data items together.
Array  =  homogenuios
struct = hetrogen

//	example

arr1 := [3]int{1, 2, 3}
arr2 := arr1   // copy happens

arr2[0] = 100

fmt.Println(arr1) // [1 2 3]
fmt.Println(arr2) // [100 2 3]



Refrence Datatype 
slice , pointers, func, maps, chanels etc...

       example

slice1 := []int{1, 2, 3}
slice2 := slice1   // reference copy

slice2[0] = 100

fmt.Println(slice1) // [100 2 3]
fmt.Println(slice2) // [100 2 3]


InterFaces 
It does not store data, it stores behavior.